Fernando Torres, Javier Hernandez and Roberto Soldado are on AC Milan's radar as they search for a replacement for Liverpool-bound striker Mario Balotelli, according to La Gazzetta dello Sport.

The Italian newspaper reports that Milan have a shortlist of six strikers, which also includes Jackson Martinez, Mattia Destro and Luis Muriel.

Balotelli is set to finalise his £16m move from the San Siro to Liverpool after flying to England to complete the switch.

